[The term "meningitis" means an inflammation of the meninges, which are the tissues that surround the brain and spinal cord, and implies lack of brain and spinal cord involvement (otherwise called encephalitis and myelitis, respectively). In viral meningitis, the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is usually visibly clear, but on laboratory examination the CSF white cell count is 6 to 500 cells per cmm, usually with lymphocytes predominating. The symptoms of viral meningitis usually last from 7 to 10 days, and the patient recovers completely.

The non-polio enteroviruses are the most common causes of viral meningitis, especially during the summer and fall months. However, other causes of viral meningitis include mumps, lymphocytic choriomeningitis viruses, arboviruses, HIV, herpes simplex virus (HSV) types 1 and 2. Some bacteria and non-infectious causes of meningitis can produce a CSF picture simulating viral meningitis. Non-infectious causes include certain drugs, such as nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) and trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole, and systemic diseases, such as lupus, sarcoidosis, and metastatic cancer.

Most people who get infected with enteroviruses are asymptomatic or have only a non-specific febrile illness. Enteroviruses are most often spread via the fecal-oral route from person to person, through fecal contamination of water or food, or contact with contaminated inanimate objects. Enteroviruses can also be spread through the respiratory secretions (saliva, sputum, or nasal mucus) of an infected person.

California Polytechnic State University, also known as Cal Poly, is a public university located in San Luis Obispo, California, United States, with almost 20 000 undergraduate and 1000 postgraduate students (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_Polytechnic_State_University). San Luis Obispo, with a population of over 45 000, is a coastal city located about midway between the California cities of Los Angeles and San Francisco (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Luis_Obispo,_California). - Mod.ML

